description: Returns the default engine and system parameter information for the cluster database engine. For more information on Amazon Aurora, see What is Amazon Aurora? in the Amazon Aurora User Guide.

parameters.name: DBParameterGroupFamily
parameters.description: The name of the DB cluster parameter group family to return engine parameter information for.

parameters.name: Filters
parameters.description: This parameter isn't currently supported. (dict) --- A filter name and value pair that is used to return a more specific list of results from a describe operation. Filters can be used to match a set of resources by specific criteria, such as IDs. The filters supported by a describe operation are documented with the describe operation. The following actions can be filtered: DescribeDBClusterBacktracks DescribeDBClusterEndpoints DescribeDBClusters DescribeDBInstances DescribeDBRecommendations DescribeDBShardGroups DescribePendingMaintenanceActions The name of the filter. Filter names are case-sensitive. One or more filter values. Filter values are case-sensitive. (string) ---

parameters.name: MaxRecords
parameters.description: The maximum number of records to include in the response. If more records exist than the specified MaxRecords value, a pagination token called a marker is included in the response so you can retrieve the remaining results. Default: 100 Constraints: Minimum 20, maximum 100.

nested_items.name: EngineDefaults
nested_items.description: Contains the result of a successful invocation of the DescribeEngineDefaultParameters action.

nested_items.name: DBParameterGroupFamily
nested_items.description: Specifies the name of the DB parameter group family that the engine default parameters apply to.

nested_items.name: Marker
nested_items.description: An optional pagination token provided by a previous EngineDefaults request. If this parameter is specified, the response includes only records beyond the marker, up to the value specified by MaxRecords .

nested_items.name: Parameters
nested_items.description: Contains a list of engine default parameters.

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: Provides a description of the parameter.

nested_items.name: Source
nested_items.description: The source of the parameter value.

nested_items.name: ApplyType
nested_items.description: Specifies the engine specific parameters type.

nested_items.name: DataType
nested_items.description: Specifies the valid data type for the parameter.

nested_items.name: AllowedValues
nested_items.description: Specifies the valid range of values for the parameter.

nested_items.name: IsModifiable
nested_items.description: Indicates whether ( true) or not ( false) the parameter can be modified. Some parameters have security or operational implications that prevent them from being changed.

nested_items.name: MinimumEngineVersion
nested_items.description: The earliest engine version to which the parameter can apply.

nested_items.name: ApplyMethod
nested_items.description: Indicates when to apply parameter updates.
